  "commentary": "With SPX at 6597.69 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 and max positive gamma at 6605, dealers are caught in a narrow 15-point volatility sandwich where they're forced to buy any dip toward 6590 and sell any rally toward 6605. The recent regime flip into PIN with massive GEX surge (215% in 1-min) indicates dealers have accumulated significant long gamma positions and will aggressively fade moves in either direction, creating strong mean-reversion dynamics. Key levels to watch: 6590 downside where dealer buying accelerates, 6605 upside where dealer selling kicks in, and the 6697 flip strike which would change the entire hedging regime if breached.\n\nBottom line: expect tight range-bound action between 6590-6605 with dealers capping both sides.",
